<!DOCTYPE task
  PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "http://docs.oasis-open.org/dita/v1.1/OS/dtd/task.dtd">
<task id="installation-instructions-all-platforms">
  <title>Install using the all platforms installer</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Installation <indexterm>all platforms version</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context>To install using the all platforms installer:<draft-comment author="Mark">The file is
        used as a common source for platform specific versions that have the right file names in
        step 5. Once DITA has local variables, this file and its variants should be consolidated and
        local variables should be used to insert the right platform-specific file
        names.</draft-comment></context>
    <steps>
      <step id="install-all.step1">
        <cmd>Create a folder named <ph product="editor">
            <filepath>oxygen</filepath> 
          </ph>
          <ph product="author">
            <filepath>oxygenAuthor</filepath>
          </ph><ph product="developer">
            <filepath>oxygenDeveloper</filepath>
          </ph>
          <ph product="svnClient">
            <filepath>syncroSVNClient</filepath>
          </ph> on your local disk.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="install-all.step2">
        <cmd>In the <ph product="editor">
            <filepath>oxygen</filepath>
          </ph>
          <ph product="author">
            <filepath>oxygenAuthor</filepath>
          </ph><ph product="developer">
            <filepath>oxygenDeveloper</filepath>
          </ph>
          <ph product="svnClient">
            <filepath>syncroSVNClient</filepath>
          </ph> folder, create a child folder named <ph keyref="minorVersion" id="minorVersion"/>
          <ph keyref="product"/>.</cmd>
        <stepresult> This creates the directory structure <ph product="editor"> /../oxygen/<ph
              conref="../topics/oxygenEntitiesDictionary.dita#OxygenEntities/minorVersion"/>/ </ph>
          <ph product="author"> /../oxygenAuthor/<ph
              conref="../topics/oxygenEntitiesDictionary.dita#OxygenEntities/minorVersion"/>/
            </ph><ph product="developer"> /../oxygenDeveloper/<ph
              conref="../topics/oxygenEntitiesDictionary.dita#OxygenEntities/minorVersion"/>/ </ph>
          <ph product="svnClient"> /../syncroSVNClient/<ph
              conref="../topics/oxygenEntitiesDictionary.dita#OxygenEntities/minorVersion"/>/
          </ph>.</stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="install-all.step3">
        <cmd>Download the all platforms installation package (<ph product="editor"
              ><filepath>oxygen.tar.gz</filepath>
          </ph>
          <ph product="author">
            <filepath>oxygenAuthor.tar.gz</filepath>
          </ph><ph product="developer">
            <filepath>oxygenDeveloper.tar.gz</filepath>
          </ph>
          <ph product="svnClient">
            <filepath>syncroSVNClient.tar.gz</filepath>
          </ph>) to this folder.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="install-all.step4">
        <cmd>Extract the archive to the same folder.</cmd>
        <stepresult><ph keyref="product"/> is now installed. </stepresult>
        
          
        
      </step>
      
      <step>
        <cmd id="install-all.step5"><draft-comment author="Mark">Presumably the way you start Oxygen and the way you enter
            your license is different when it is installed on a server. How is it done in these
            cases?</draft-comment>Start <ph keyref="product"/> by running <ph product="editor"
              ><filepath>oxygen.XXX</filepath></ph><ph product="author"
              ><filepath>oxygenAuthor.XXX</filepath></ph><ph product="developer"
              ><filepath>oxygenDeveloper.XXX</filepath></ph><ph product="svnClient"
              ><filepath>syncroSVNClient.XXX</filepath></ph>, which is located in the install
          folder. </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="install-all.step6">
        <cmd>To license your copy of <ph keyref="product"/> go to <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Help</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Register...</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> and enter your <xref keyref="install.license-key">license key</xref>.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
